(2019, Beiya Hospital, Jiangzhou, China)

39
00:05:09,650 --> 00:05:10,580
It's finished?

40
00:05:13,140 --> 00:05:14,020
Yes.

41
00:05:14,650 --> 00:05:15,650
Coffee?

42
00:05:16,490 --> 00:05:17,170
No.

43
00:05:17,330 --> 00:05:17,980
Thanks.

44
00:05:37,220 --> 00:05:39,900
(Beiya Hospital)

45
00:05:56,490 --> 00:05:57,820
Where have you guys been
these past two days?

46
00:05:57,820 --> 00:05:58,820
We couldn't reach you.

47
00:05:59,890 --> 00:06:00,580
What's going on here?

48
00:06:01,330 --> 00:06:03,490
I just haven't come
to see my mother in a few days.

49
00:06:04,170 --> 00:06:05,050
How did she end up like this?

50
00:06:05,300 --> 00:06:07,580
Your mother fell down in the stairwell

51
00:06:07,580 --> 00:06:08,490
and fainted.

52
00:06:08,490 --> 00:06:09,700
We had to operate on her.

53
00:06:09,860 --> 00:06:11,820
She fell and fainted?

54
00:06:13,980 --> 00:06:15,140
This isn't right.

55
00:06:15,610 --> 00:06:17,980
My mother was fine in the hospital.

56
00:06:17,980 --> 00:06:19,330
How could she just fall all of a sudden?

57
00:06:21,770 --> 00:06:22,770
I know.

58
00:06:22,770 --> 00:06:24,610
You were resentful and did this

59
00:06:24,930 --> 00:06:27,100
because I complained about you.

60
00:06:27,100 --> 00:06:28,300
You abused my mother!

61
00:06:29,490 --> 00:06:30,420
This is a ward.

62
00:06:30,420 --> 00:06:31,650
Patients need rest in here.

63
00:06:31,650 --> 00:06:32,650
Let's step outside to talk.

64
00:06:33,770 --> 00:06:35,580
What can't we talk about here?

65
00:06:35,580 --> 00:06:36,540
Are you trying to hide something?

66
00:06:36,540 --> 00:06:37,420
What are you doing?

67
00:06:37,860 --> 00:06:39,050
How could you lay a hand on a doctor?

68
00:06:39,050 --> 00:06:39,580
Move aside!

69
00:06:40,170 --> 00:06:41,890
Try touching me again, and you'll see.

70
00:06:41,980 --> 00:06:43,100
- So what?
- Calm down.

71
00:06:43,860 --> 00:06:44,700
I'll even hit you!

72
00:06:48,260 --> 00:06:49,210
What's the matter with you?

73
00:06:49,740 --> 00:06:51,260
We just had a meeting a few days ago

74
00:06:51,820 --> 00:06:53,260
about doctor-patient relations.

75
00:06:53,490 --> 00:06:54,210
But look at you.

76
00:06:54,450 --> 00:06:55,650
Look what happened today.

77
00:06:55,650 --> 00:06:57,770
You took the lead in this mess.

78
00:06:57,770 --> 00:06:58,700
- Manager Liu.
- Manager Liu.

79
00:07:00,330 --> 00:07:01,490
(Beiya Hospital)
Don't defend him.

80
00:07:01,820 --> 00:07:03,100
I know all about what happened.

81
00:07:03,540 --> 00:07:04,580
Violence is wrong no matter what.

82
00:07:04,580 --> 00:07:06,020
Well, we can't just let him attack us.

83
00:07:06,260 --> 00:07:07,490
Besides, he assaulted us first.

84
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:09,420
That's enough from you two.

85
00:07:10,260 --> 00:07:11,140
Who knows

86
00:07:11,370 --> 00:07:12,490
how we're going to settle this matter?

87
00:07:12,860 --> 00:07:14,300
Now I have to clean up your mess.

88
00:07:19,540 --> 00:07:21,450
Take this as a lesson, everyone.

89
00:07:22,020 --> 00:07:23,700
Don't engage
when something like this happens.

90
00:07:24,450 --> 00:07:25,740
You're a doctor.

91
00:07:25,860 --> 00:07:27,170
Don't you even know
where the vitals are?

92
00:07:27,650 --> 00:07:29,100
Stop checking in the mirror.
Your looks are ruined.

93
00:07:29,450 --> 00:07:30,490
It's not that bad.

94
00:07:31,020 --> 00:07:31,610
Dr. Ruan,

95
00:07:31,610 --> 00:07:32,820
what's wrong with you?

96
00:07:32,820 --> 00:07:34,140
Didn't I tell you to get out of there?

97
00:07:34,170 --> 00:07:35,490
Why did you stay?

98
00:07:35,490 --> 00:07:36,580
To let him catch you?

99
00:07:36,700 --> 00:07:38,580
I wanted to help you.

100
00:07:38,890 --> 00:07:40,260
There must've been other ways
to resolve this.

101
00:07:40,260 --> 00:07:41,330
Why couldn't you hold back?

102
00:07:41,740 --> 00:07:42,650
How?

103
00:07:42,650 --> 00:07:43,930
Should I let him strangle you to death?

104
00:07:44,860 --> 00:07:45,580
Ding Yiyuan.

105
00:07:45,930 --> 00:07:46,540
What?

106
00:07:48,050 --> 00:07:49,330
Thanks.

107
00:07:49,770 --> 00:07:50,650
Thanks?

108
00:07:50,650 --> 00:07:51,700
For what?

109
00:07:51,860 --> 00:07:52,860
For helping you fight him off?

110
00:07:54,210 --> 00:07:55,170
You could say that.

111
00:07:56,740 --> 00:07:58,770
You're the one not to be underestimated.

112
00:07:59,330 --> 00:08:01,210
You said all those things this morning.

113
00:08:01,210 --> 00:08:02,860
You were completely different
from your usual self.

114
00:08:03,580 --> 00:08:05,140
Even a rabbit
will bite when it's cornered.

115
00:08:06,050 --> 00:08:07,450
No need to thank me.

116
00:08:08,300 --> 00:08:10,260
I didn't do it because I like you.

117
00:08:10,650 --> 00:08:12,210
We're all doctors.

118
00:08:12,210 --> 00:08:13,490
If that could happen to you today,

119
00:08:13,490 --> 00:08:15,580
it might happen to me next time.

120
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:18,020
Helping you is helping myself.

121
00:08:18,140 --> 00:08:19,330
Okay.

122
00:08:19,450 --> 00:08:20,890
But still, thank you.

123
00:08:21,370 --> 00:08:23,820
I learned something
from my observation today.

124
00:08:24,140 --> 00:08:24,860
What?

125
00:08:28,580 --> 00:08:30,300
Are you and Mr. Ning together?

126
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:33,210
No.

127
00:08:34,380 --> 00:08:35,210
No?

128
00:08:35,890 --> 00:08:37,650
He got so upset because of you.

129
00:08:37,650 --> 00:08:38,860
Do you think that's normal?

130
00:08:38,980 --> 00:08:40,890
It sounded like he was lecturing you,

131
00:08:40,890 --> 00:08:42,420
but something seemed off.

132
00:08:43,060 --> 00:08:44,100
How so?

133
00:08:44,180 --> 00:08:45,330
Ruan Liuzheng, listen here.

134
00:08:45,330 --> 00:08:46,330
I know you like him.

135
00:08:46,860 --> 00:08:48,740
And you might've beaten me to him.

136
00:08:50,450 --> 00:08:51,420
Are you laughing at me?

137
00:08:52,100 --> 00:08:52,810
No.

138
00:08:53,380 --> 00:08:54,420
But I'm not worried.

139
00:08:54,860 --> 00:08:56,980
I'm a person of honor and integrity.

140
00:08:57,450 --> 00:08:58,890
I don't hide my intentions.

141
00:08:59,100 --> 00:09:00,010
As long as he is single,

142
00:09:00,010 --> 00:09:01,500
I have the right to pursue him.

143
00:09:02,010 --> 00:09:02,740
Got it?

144
00:09:02,980 --> 00:09:03,690
Got it.

145
00:09:05,980 --> 00:09:07,210
Wait for me.

146
00:09:07,220 --> 00:09:10,540
(Beiya Hospital)

147
00:09:16,860 --> 00:09:18,860
I heard Madam Cai's family
lodged a complaint.

148
00:09:19,330 --> 00:09:20,420
Let it be.

149
00:09:22,250 --> 00:09:23,690
What if they actually
take disciplinary actions against you?

150
00:09:24,980 --> 00:09:26,180
Let them do it.

151
00:09:27,690 --> 00:09:28,380
All right.

152
00:09:28,450 --> 00:09:29,450
Pretend I never said anything.

153
00:09:31,420 --> 00:09:31,860
Dr. Ning.

154
00:09:34,130 --> 00:09:35,380
Can you still drive?

155
00:09:35,770 --> 00:09:36,540
No.

156
00:09:36,690 --> 00:09:37,570
Why don't you drive?

157
00:09:37,770 --> 00:09:38,690
You're self-aware.

158
00:09:38,690 --> 00:09:39,420
It's those two, right?

159
00:09:45,130 --> 00:09:45,770
Thank you.

160
00:10:29,450 --> 00:10:30,530
Mr. Ning, we're here.

161
00:10:31,770 --> 00:10:32,720
I'll leave now.

162
00:10:32,920 --> 00:10:33,890
Wait here.

163
00:10:33,890 --> 00:10:34,970
I'll go get him.

164
00:10:34,970 --> 00:10:36,240
Let's send him home first.

165
00:10:44,970 --> 00:10:45,600
Were you a good boy today?

166
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:46,510
(Jiangzhou Zhengyang District
Cosmo Bilingual Kindergarten)

167
00:10:47,210 --> 00:10:48,800
Mom!

168
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:52,090
Mom!

169
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:53,720
Mom! You came to pick me up!

170
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:55,480
I'm so happy!

171
00:10:56,650 --> 00:10:57,240
Let's go.

172
00:10:59,120 --> 00:11:01,290
I missed you so much, Mom.

173
00:11:01,290 --> 00:11:02,480
Did you miss me?

174
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:04,560
I missed you too.

175
00:11:05,240 --> 00:11:05,770
Mom,

176
00:11:05,770 --> 00:11:07,920
I have a present for you.

177
00:11:07,920 --> 00:11:08,650
What is it?

178
00:11:08,650 --> 00:11:11,530
My teacher said
Mother's Day is on Sunday.

179
00:11:11,560 --> 00:11:12,920
This is for you.

180
00:11:15,890 --> 00:11:16,560
That's so nice.

181
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:17,360
Thank you.

182
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:20,480
Mom, if Dad gave you flowers,

183
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:22,040
would you accept him too?

184
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:30,090
Ning Xiang,

185
00:11:30,090 --> 00:11:30,970
if you keep saying nonsense,

186
00:11:30,970 --> 00:11:32,330
your mom won't pick you up anymore.

187
00:11:33,650 --> 00:11:34,720
You're mean, Dad.

188
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:43,680
You're so pretty, Mom.

189
00:11:43,720 --> 00:11:45,120
I love you.

190
00:11:45,330 --> 00:11:47,120
Oh, what a sweet talker you are.

191
00:11:48,650 --> 00:11:50,720
Bounce and bounce
goes the yellow flower.

192
00:11:51,160 --> 00:11:52,850
Bouncing to the sky.

193
00:12:03,850 --> 00:12:04,450
Mom.

194
00:12:05,770 --> 00:12:06,560
Liuzheng.

195
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:08,680
(23 Huangxian Road)
You're home early today.

196
00:12:09,410 --> 00:12:10,890
Who brought you home?

197
00:12:12,360 --> 00:12:13,330
Zhiqian?

198
00:12:16,330 --> 00:12:17,010
(Huangxian Road)
Mom.

199
00:12:18,160 --> 00:12:19,160
This is my son.

200
00:12:19,970 --> 00:12:20,920
- Son?
- Greet your grandma.

201
00:12:20,920 --> 00:12:22,010
Grandma.

202
00:12:22,090 --> 00:12:22,920
Hello.

203
00:12:23,240 --> 00:12:24,650
I'm Ning Xiang.

204
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:26,720
Ning Xiang?

205
00:12:27,650 --> 00:12:28,800
You're a handsome boy.

206
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:29,650
How old are you?

207
00:12:29,650 --> 00:12:30,480
Six.

208
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:38,160
Let's not stand out here.

209
00:12:38,160 --> 00:12:39,090
Let's go inside.

210
00:12:39,450 --> 00:12:40,040
Come on.

211
00:12:41,450 --> 00:12:42,210
Dad,

212
00:12:42,770 --> 00:12:45,560
Grandma is my mom's mom, right?

213
00:12:46,090 --> 00:12:46,680
Yes.

214
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:49,210
Come in.

215
00:12:49,530 --> 00:12:50,560
Dear,

216
00:12:50,720 --> 00:12:51,970
look who's here.

217
00:12:54,970 --> 00:12:55,850
Oh, Zhiqian is here.

218
00:12:57,040 --> 00:12:58,240
And who is this little boy?

219
00:12:58,240 --> 00:12:59,560
I'm Ning Xiang.

220
00:12:59,560 --> 00:13:00,800
I'm six.

221
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:01,650
This is my son.

222
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:02,530
Ning Xiang?

223
00:13:02,530 --> 00:13:03,160
Six?

224
00:13:03,770 --> 00:13:04,330
Greet your grandpa.

225
00:13:04,410 --> 00:13:05,360
Grandpa.

226
00:13:05,360 --> 00:13:06,120
Hello.

227
00:13:06,240 --> 00:13:06,800
Come in.

228
00:13:07,040 --> 00:13:09,010
You have gold fish!

229
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:10,560
- Yes.
- Ning Xiang!

230
00:13:10,720 --> 00:13:11,530
- Don't be naughty.
- Here.

231
00:13:11,530 --> 00:13:12,360
Like this.

232
00:13:12,360 --> 00:13:13,450
You can feed them.

233
00:13:15,650 --> 00:13:16,240
Zhiqian,

234
00:13:16,680 --> 00:13:18,120
will you have dinner with us?

235
00:13:18,450 --> 00:13:19,040
Mom,

236
00:13:19,450 --> 00:13:21,040
Mr. Ning has something to do tonight.

237
00:13:21,040 --> 00:13:22,040
Don't trouble him.

238
00:13:22,850 --> 00:13:23,530
Mom,

239
00:13:23,680 --> 00:13:26,090
why do you call Dad "Mr. Ning"?

240
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:28,010
The other kids' moms call their husbands

241
00:13:28,010 --> 00:13:29,560
"dear".

242
00:13:40,090 --> 00:13:41,240
Right. Ning Xiang.

243
00:13:41,240 --> 00:13:42,360
- I'll go get changed
- Come here.

244
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:43,210
- and help you.
- Come here.

245
00:13:43,210 --> 00:13:44,850
- Have a seat, Mr. Ning.
- I've got a set of Xiangqi.

246
00:13:44,850 --> 00:13:46,330
- Let's play it.
- Have some water, Zhiqian.

247
00:13:46,330 --> 00:13:47,160
How are you?

248
00:13:49,160 --> 00:13:50,240
Let me tell you something.

249
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:51,770
Xiangqi has a set of rules

250
00:13:51,770 --> 00:13:53,290
that dictate

251
00:13:53,290 --> 00:13:54,040
how the pieces move.

252
00:13:54,040 --> 00:13:57,650
The Horse moves diagonally of a square,
and the Elephant of a double-girds square.

253
00:13:57,650 --> 00:13:59,000
The General doesn't leave

254
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:00,840
- the back garden.
- The back garden.

255
00:14:01,210 --> 00:14:02,530
Oh, you know the rules.

256
00:14:03,210 --> 00:14:05,680
I'm taking your General!

257
00:14:05,680 --> 00:14:06,890
No, no, no.

258
00:14:06,890 --> 00:14:07,600
That won't do.

259
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:09,120
I must hide it.

260
00:14:10,720 --> 00:14:12,650
- Here.
- Then, I'll take this piece.

261
00:14:12,650 --> 00:14:13,290
(Tea)
You act fast.

262
00:14:13,290 --> 00:14:14,850
I'll take your piece here.

263
00:14:16,010 --> 00:14:17,090
You took another one of mine.

264
00:14:17,090 --> 00:14:18,410
Can you remember it now?

265
00:14:18,410 --> 00:14:19,450
Say it out loud.

266
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:20,450
Come.

267
00:14:20,680 --> 00:14:23,240
The Horse moves diagonally of a square.

268
00:14:24,120 --> 00:14:26,330
The Elephant moves diagonally
of a double-girds square.

269
00:14:27,330 --> 00:14:30,240
The Chariot takes the straight path.
The cannon goes over the hill.

270
00:14:30,240 --> 00:14:31,650
- Which piece is the Elephant?
- The General...

271
00:14:31,800 --> 00:14:32,680
This one.

272
00:14:32,680 --> 00:14:33,210
This one?

273
00:14:33,210 --> 00:14:33,890
Yes.

274
00:14:34,360 --> 00:14:35,210
You know it now.

275
00:14:36,010 --> 00:14:36,650
Not bad.

276
00:14:57,410 --> 00:14:59,410
I'll be waiting for you to come back.
It's a promise.

277
00:15:00,160 --> 00:15:01,680
- Say goodbye.
- Goodbye, Grandma, Grandpa.

278
00:15:01,680 --> 00:15:02,330
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

279
00:15:02,410 --> 00:15:03,120
Goodbye.

280
00:15:03,450 --> 00:15:04,600
Goodbye, Mom.

281
00:15:05,160 --> 00:15:07,970
Aren't you coming home with Dad and me?

282
00:15:13,800 --> 00:15:15,160
Um, we'll be leaving now.

283
00:15:15,160 --> 00:15:15,970
Okay.

284
00:15:18,330 --> 00:15:19,330
See you, Zhiqian.

